173  // Prepare information for eager deoptimization. This information is carried
174  // by dedicated {Checkpoint} nodes that are wired into the effect chain.
175  // Conceptually this frame state is "before" a given operation.
176  void PrepareEagerCheckpoint();
177 
178  // Prepare information for lazy deoptimization. This information is attached
179  // to the given node and the output value produced by the node is combined.
180  //
181  // The low-level chokepoint - use the variants below instead.
182  void PrepareFrameState(Node* node, OutputFrameStateCombine combine,
183  BytecodeOffset bailout_id,
184  const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness);
185 
186  // In the common case, frame states are conceptually "after" a given
187  // operation and at the current bytecode offset.
188  void PrepareFrameState(Node* node, OutputFrameStateCombine combine) {
189  if (!OperatorProperties::HasFrameStateInput(node->op())) return;
190  const int offset = bytecode_iterator().current_offset();
191  return PrepareFrameState(node, combine, BytecodeOffset(offset),
192  bytecode_analysis().GetOutLivenessFor(offset));
193  }
194 
195  // For function-entry stack checks, they're conceptually "before" the first
196  // bytecode and at a special marker bytecode offset.
197  // In the case of FE stack checks, the current bytecode is also the first
198  // bytecode, so we use a special marker bytecode offset to signify a virtual
199  // bytecode before the first physical bytecode.
200  void PrepareFrameStateForFunctionEntryStackCheck(Node* node) {
201  DCHECK_EQ(bytecode_iterator().current_offset(), 0);
202  DCHECK(OperatorProperties::HasFrameStateInput(node->op()));
203  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSStackCheck);
204  return PrepareFrameState(node, OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore(),
205  BytecodeOffset(kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset),
206  bytecode_analysis().GetInLivenessFor(0));
207  }
208 
209  // For OSR-entry stack checks, they're conceptually "before" the first
210  // bytecode of the current loop. We implement this in a similar manner to
211  // function-entry (FE) stack checks above, i.e. we deopt at the predecessor
212  // of the current bytecode.
213  // In the case of OSR-entry stack checks, a physical predecessor bytecode
214  // exists: the JumpLoop bytecode. We attach to JumpLoop by using
215  // `bytecode_analysis().osr_bailout_id()` instead of current_offset (the
216  // former points at JumpLoop, the latter at the loop header, i.e. the target
217  // of JumpLoop).
218  void PrepareFrameStateForOSREntryStackCheck(Node* node) {
219  DCHECK(OperatorProperties::HasFrameStateInput(node->op()));
220  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSStackCheck);
221  const int offset = bytecode_analysis().osr_bailout_id().ToInt();
222  return PrepareFrameState(node, OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore(),
223  BytecodeOffset(offset),
224  bytecode_analysis().GetOutLivenessFor(offset));
225  }

371  // An abstract representation for an exception handler that is being
372  // entered and exited while the graph builder is iterating over the
373  // underlying bytecode. The exception handlers within the bytecode are
374  // well scoped, hence will form a stack during iteration.
375  struct ExceptionHandler {
376  int start_offset_; // Start offset of the handled area in the bytecode.
377  int end_offset_; // End offset of the handled area in the bytecode.
378  int handler_offset_; // Handler entry offset within the bytecode.
379  int context_register_; // Index of register holding handler context.
380  };

382  template <class T = Object>
383  typename ref_traits<T>::ref_type MakeRefForConstantForIndexOperand(
384  int operand_index) {
385  // The BytecodeArray itself was fetched by using a barrier so all reads
386  // from the constant pool are safe.
387  return MakeRefAssumeMemoryFence(
388  broker(), broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
389  Cast<T>(bytecode_iterator().GetConstantForIndexOperand(
390  operand_index, local_isolate_))));
391  }

645 // Issues:
646 // - Scopes - intimately tied to AST. Need to eval what is needed.
647 // - Need to resolve closure parameter treatment.
648 BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment::Environment(
649  BytecodeGraphBuilder* builder, int register_count, int parameter_count,
650  interpreter::Register incoming_new_target_or_generator,
651  Node* control_dependency)
652  : builder_(builder),
653  register_count_(register_count),
654  parameter_count_(parameter_count),
655  control_dependency_(control_dependency),
656  effect_dependency_(control_dependency),
657  values_(builder->local_zone()),
658  parameters_state_values_(nullptr),
659  generator_state_(nullptr) {
660  // The layout of values_ is:
661  //
662  // [receiver] [parameters] [registers] [accumulator]
663  //
664  // parameter[0] is the receiver (this), parameters 1..N are the
665  // parameters supplied to the method (arg0..argN-1). The accumulator
666  // is stored separately.
667 
668  // Parameters including the receiver
669  for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count; i++) {
670  const char* debug_name = (i == 0) ? "%this" : nullptr;
671  Node* parameter = builder->GetParameter(i, debug_name);
672  values()->push_back(parameter);
673  }
674 
675  // Registers
676  register_base_ = static_cast<int>(values()->size());
677  Node* undefined_constant = builder->jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
678  values()->insert(values()->end(), register_count, undefined_constant);
679 
680  // Accumulator
681  accumulator_base_ = static_cast<int>(values()->size());
682  values()->push_back(undefined_constant);
683 
684  // Context
685  int context_index = Linkage::GetJSCallContextParamIndex(parameter_count);
686  context_ = builder->GetParameter(context_index, "%context");
687 
688  // Incoming new.target or generator register
689  if (incoming_new_target_or_generator.is_valid()) {
690  int new_target_index =
691  Linkage::GetJSCallNewTargetParamIndex(parameter_count);
692  Node* new_target_node =
693  builder->GetParameter(new_target_index, "%new.target");
694 
695  int values_index = RegisterToValuesIndex(incoming_new_target_or_generator);
696  values()->at(values_index) = new_target_node;
697  }
698 }

795 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment::Merge(
796  BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment* other,
797  const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness) {
798  // Create a merge of the control dependencies of both environments and update
799  // the current environment's control dependency accordingly.
800  Node* control = builder()->MergeControl(GetControlDependency(),
801  other->GetControlDependency());
802  UpdateControlDependency(control);
803 
804  // Create a merge of the effect dependencies of both environments and update
805  // the current environment's effect dependency accordingly.
806  Node* effect = builder()->MergeEffect(GetEffectDependency(),
807  other->GetEffectDependency(), control);
808  UpdateEffectDependency(effect);
809 
810  // Introduce Phi nodes for values that are live and have differing inputs at
811  // the merge point, potentially extending an existing Phi node if possible.
812  context_ = builder()->MergeValue(context_, other->context_, control);
813  for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count(); i++) {
814  values_[i] = builder()->MergeValue(values_[i], other->values_[i], control);
815  }
816  for (int i = 0; i < register_count(); i++) {
817  int index = register_base() + i;
818  if (liveness == nullptr || liveness->RegisterIsLive(i)) {
819 #if DEBUG
820  // We only do these DCHECKs when we are not in the resume path of a
821  // generator -- this is, when either there is no generator state at all,
822  // or the generator state is not the constant "executing" value.
823  if (generator_state_ == nullptr ||
824  NumberMatcher(generator_state_)
825  .Is(JSGeneratorObject::kGeneratorExecuting)) {
826  DCHECK_NE(values_[index], builder()->jsgraph()->OptimizedOutConstant());
827  DCHECK_NE(other->values_[index],
828  builder()->jsgraph()->OptimizedOutConstant());
829  }
830 #endif
831 
832  values_[index] =
833  builder()->MergeValue(values_[index], other->values_[index], control);
834 
835  } else {
836  values_[index] = builder()->jsgraph()->OptimizedOutConstant();
837  }
838  }
839 
840  if (liveness == nullptr || liveness->AccumulatorIsLive()) {
841  DCHECK_NE(values_[accumulator_base()],
842  builder()->jsgraph()->OptimizedOutConstant());
843  DCHECK_NE(other->values_[accumulator_base()],
844  builder()->jsgraph()->OptimizedOutConstant());
845 
846  values_[accumulator_base()] =
847  builder()->MergeValue(values_[accumulator_base()],
848  other->values_[accumulator_base()], control);
849  } else {
850  values_[accumulator_base()] = builder()->jsgraph()->OptimizedOutConstant();
851  }
852 
853  if (generator_state_ != nullptr) {
854  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(other->generator_state_);
855  generator_state_ = builder()->MergeValue(generator_state_,
856  other->generator_state_, control);
857  }
858 }
859 
860 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment::PrepareForLoop(
861  const BytecodeLoopAssignments& assignments,
862  const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness) {
863  // Create a control node for the loop header.
864  Node* control = builder()->NewLoop();
865 
866  // Create a Phi for external effects.
867  Node* effect = builder()->NewEffectPhi(1, GetEffectDependency(), control);
868  UpdateEffectDependency(effect);
869 
870  // Create Phis for any values that are live on entry to the loop and may be
871  // updated by the end of the loop.
872  context_ = builder()->NewPhi(1, context_, control);
873  for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count(); i++) {
874  if (assignments.ContainsParameter(i)) {
875  values_[i] = builder()->NewPhi(1, values_[i], control);
876  }
877  }
878  for (int i = 0; i < register_count(); i++) {
879  if (assignments.ContainsLocal(i) &&
880  (liveness == nullptr || liveness->RegisterIsLive(i))) {
881  int index = register_base() + i;
882  values_[index] = builder()->NewPhi(1, values_[index], control);
883  }
884  }
885  // The accumulator should not be live on entry.
886  DCHECK_IMPLIES(liveness != nullptr, !liveness->AccumulatorIsLive());
887 
888  if (generator_state_ != nullptr) {
889  generator_state_ = builder()->NewPhi(1, generator_state_, control);
890  }
891 
892  // Connect to the loop end.
893  Node* terminate = builder()->graph()->NewNode(
894  builder()->common()->Terminate(), effect, control);
895  builder()->exit_controls_.push_back(terminate);
896 }
897 
898 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment::FillWithOsrValues() {
899  Node* start = graph()->start();
900 
901  // Create OSR values for each environment value.
902  SetContext(graph()->NewNode(
903  common()->OsrValue(Linkage::kOsrContextSpillSlotIndex), start));
904  int size = static_cast<int>(values()->size());
905  for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
906  int idx = i; // Indexing scheme follows {StandardFrame}, adapt accordingly.
907  if (i >= register_base()) idx += InterpreterFrameConstants::kExtraSlotCount;
908  if (i >= accumulator_base()) idx = Linkage::kOsrAccumulatorRegisterIndex;
909  values()->at(i) = graph()->NewNode(common()->OsrValue(idx), start);
910  }
911 }

913 bool BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment::StateValuesRequireUpdate(
914  Node** state_values, Node** values, int count) {
915  if (*state_values == nullptr) {
916  return true;
917  }
918  Node::Inputs inputs = (*state_values)->inputs();
919  if (inputs.count() != count) return true;
920  for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
921  if (inputs[i] != values[i]) {
922  return true;
923  }
924  }
925  return false;
926 }

928 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment::PrepareForLoopExit(
929  Node* loop, const BytecodeLoopAssignments& assignments,
930  const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness) {
931  DCHECK_EQ(loop->opcode(), IrOpcode::kLoop);
932 
933  Node* control = GetControlDependency();
934 
935  // Create the loop exit node.
936  Node* loop_exit = graph()->NewNode(common()->LoopExit(), control, loop);
937  UpdateControlDependency(loop_exit);
938 
939  // Rename the effect.
940  Node* effect_rename = graph()->NewNode(common()->LoopExitEffect(),
941  GetEffectDependency(), loop_exit);
942  UpdateEffectDependency(effect_rename);
943 
944  // TODO(jarin) We should also rename context here. However, unconditional
945  // renaming confuses global object and native context specialization.
946  // We should only rename if the context is assigned in the loop.
947 
948  // Rename the environment values if they were assigned in the loop and are
949  // live after exiting the loop.
950  for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count(); i++) {
951  if (assignments.ContainsParameter(i)) {
952  Node* rename = graph()->NewNode(
953  common()->LoopExitValue(MachineRepresentation::kTagged), values_[i],
954  loop_exit);
955  values_[i] = rename;
956  }
957  }
958  for (int i = 0; i < register_count(); i++) {
959  if (assignments.ContainsLocal(i) &&
960  (liveness == nullptr || liveness->RegisterIsLive(i))) {
961  Node* rename = graph()->NewNode(
962  common()->LoopExitValue(MachineRepresentation::kTagged),
963  values_[register_base() + i], loop_exit);
964  values_[register_base() + i] = rename;
965  }
966  }
967  if (liveness == nullptr || liveness->AccumulatorIsLive()) {
968  Node* rename = graph()->NewNode(
969  common()->LoopExitValue(MachineRepresentation::kTagged),
970  values_[accumulator_base()], loop_exit);
971  values_[accumulator_base()] = rename;
972  }
973 
974  if (generator_state_ != nullptr) {
975  generator_state_ = graph()->NewNode(
976  common()->LoopExitValue(MachineRepresentation::kTagged),
977  generator_state_, loop_exit);
978  }
979 }

981 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment::UpdateStateValues(Node** state_values,
982  Node** values,
983  int count) {
984  if (StateValuesRequireUpdate(state_values, values, count)) {

986  (*state_values) = graph()->NewNode(op, count, values);

996 Node* BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment::Checkpoint(
997  BytecodeOffset bailout_id, OutputFrameStateCombine combine,
998  const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness) {
999  if (parameter_count() == register_count()) {
1000  // Reuse the state-value cache if the number of local registers happens
1001  // to match the parameter count.
1002  parameters_state_values_ =
1003  GetStateValuesFromCache(&values()->at(0), parameter_count(), nullptr);
1004  } else {
1005  UpdateStateValues(&parameters_state_values_, &values()->at(0),
1006  parameter_count());
1007  }
1008 
1009  Node* registers_state_values = GetStateValuesFromCache(
1010  &values()->at(register_base()), register_count(), liveness);
1011 
1012  bool accumulator_is_live = !liveness || liveness->AccumulatorIsLive();
1013  Node* accumulator_state_value =
1014  accumulator_is_live && combine != OutputFrameStateCombine::PokeAt(0)
1015  ? values()->at(accumulator_base())
1016  : builder()->jsgraph()->OptimizedOutConstant();
1017 
1018  const Operator* op = common()->FrameState(
1019  bailout_id, combine, builder()->frame_state_function_info());
1020  Node* result = graph()->NewNode(
1021  op, parameters_state_values_, registers_state_values,
1022  accumulator_state_value, Context(), builder()->GetFunctionClosure(),
1023  builder()->graph()->start());
1024 
1025  return result;
1026 }

1162 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::CreateGraph() {
1163  SourcePositionTable::Scope pos_scope(source_positions_, start_position_);
1164  if (node_origins_) {
1165  AddBytecodePositionDecorator();
1166  }
1167  // Set up the basic structure of the graph. Outputs for {Start} are the formal
1168  // parameters (including the receiver) plus new target, number of arguments,
1169  // context and closure.
1170  int start_output_arity = StartNode::OutputArityForFormalParameterCount(
1171  bytecode_array().parameter_count());
1172  graph()->SetStart(graph()->NewNode(common()->Start(start_output_arity)));
1173 
1174  Environment env(this, bytecode_array().register_count(),
1175  bytecode_array().parameter_count(),
1176  bytecode_array().incoming_new_target_or_generator_register(),
1177  graph()->start());
1178  set_environment(&env);
1179 
1180  CreateFeedbackVectorNode();
1181  CreateNativeContextNode();
1182 
1183  VisitBytecodes();
1184 
1185  // Finish the basic structure of the graph.
1186  DCHECK_NE(0u, exit_controls_.size());
1187  int const input_count = static_cast<int>(exit_controls_.size());
1188  Node** const inputs = &exit_controls_.front();
1189  Node* end = graph()->NewNode(common()->End(input_count), input_count, inputs);
1190  graph()->SetEnd(end);
1191  if (node_origins_) {
1192  RemoveBytecodePositionDecorator();
1193  }
1194 }

1196 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::PrepareEagerCheckpoint() {
1197  if (needs_eager_checkpoint()) {
1198  // Create an explicit checkpoint node for before the operation. This only
1199  // needs to happen if we aren't effect-dominated by a {Checkpoint} already.
1200  mark_as_needing_eager_checkpoint(false);
1201  Node* node = NewNode(common()->Checkpoint());
1202  DCHECK_EQ(1, OperatorProperties::GetFrameStateInputCount(node->op()));
1203  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kDead,
1204  NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node)->opcode());
1205  BytecodeOffset bailout_id(bytecode_iterator().current_offset());
1206 
1207  const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness_before =
1208  bytecode_analysis().GetInLivenessFor(
1209  bytecode_iterator().current_offset());
1210 
1211  Node* frame_state_before = environment()->Checkpoint(
1212  bailout_id, OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore(), liveness_before);
1213  NodeProperties::ReplaceFrameStateInput(node, frame_state_before);
1214 #ifdef DEBUG
1215  } else {
1216  // In case we skipped checkpoint creation above, we must be able to find an
1217  // existing checkpoint that effect-dominates the nodes about to be created.
1218  // Starting a search from the current effect-dependency has to succeed.
1219  Node* effect = environment()->GetEffectDependency();
1220  while (effect->opcode() != IrOpcode::kCheckpoint) {
1221  DCHECK(effect->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoWrite));
1222  DCHECK_EQ(1, effect->op()->EffectInputCount());
1223  effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(effect);
1224  }
1225  }
1226 #else
1227  }
1228 #endif // DEBUG
1229 }

1231 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::PrepareFrameState(
1232  Node* node, OutputFrameStateCombine combine, BytecodeOffset bailout_id,
1233  const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness) {
1234  if (OperatorProperties::HasFrameStateInput(node->op())) {
1235  // Add the frame state for after the operation. The node in question has
1236  // already been created and had a {Dead} frame state input up until now.
1237  DCHECK_EQ(1, OperatorProperties::GetFrameStateInputCount(node->op()));
1238  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kDead,
1239  NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node)->opcode());
1240 
1241  Node* frame_state_after =
1242  environment()->Checkpoint(bailout_id, combine, liveness);
1243  NodeProperties::ReplaceFrameStateInput(node, frame_state_after);
1244  }
1245 }

1247 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::AdvanceIteratorsTo(int bytecode_offset) {
1248  for (; bytecode_iterator().current_offset() != bytecode_offset;
1249  bytecode_iterator().Advance()) {
1250  int current_offset = bytecode_iterator().current_offset();
1251  UpdateSourceAndBytecodePosition(current_offset);
1252  }
1253 }
1254 
1255 // Stores the state of the SourcePosition iterator, and the index to the
1256 // current exception handlers stack. We need, during the OSR graph generation,
1257 // to backup the states of these iterators at the LoopHeader offset of each
1258 // outer loop which contains the OSR loop. The iterators are then restored when
1259 // peeling the loops, so that both exception handling and synchronisation with
1260 // the source position can be achieved.
1261 class BytecodeGraphBuilder::OsrIteratorState {
1262  public:
1263  explicit OsrIteratorState(BytecodeGraphBuilder* graph_builder)
1264  : graph_builder_(graph_builder),
1265  saved_states_(graph_builder->local_zone()) {}
1266 
1267  void ProcessOsrPrelude() {
1268  ZoneVector<int> outer_loop_offsets(graph_builder_->local_zone());
1269  int osr_entry = graph_builder_->bytecode_analysis().osr_entry_point();
1270 
1271  // We find here the outermost loop which contains the OSR loop.
1272  int outermost_loop_offset = osr_entry;
1273  while ((outermost_loop_offset = graph_builder_->bytecode_analysis()
1274  .GetLoopInfoFor(outermost_loop_offset)
1275  .parent_offset()) != -1) {
1276  outer_loop_offsets.push_back(outermost_loop_offset);
1277  }
1278  outermost_loop_offset =
1279  outer_loop_offsets.empty() ? osr_entry : outer_loop_offsets.back();
1280  graph_builder_->AdvanceIteratorsTo(outermost_loop_offset);
1281 
1282  // We save some iterators states at the offsets of the loop headers of the
1283  // outer loops (the ones containing the OSR loop). They will be used for
1284  // jumping back in the bytecode.
1285  for (ZoneVector<int>::const_reverse_iterator it =
1286  outer_loop_offsets.crbegin();
1287  it != outer_loop_offsets.crend(); ++it) {
1288  graph_builder_->AdvanceIteratorsTo(*it);
1289  graph_builder_->ExitThenEnterExceptionHandlers(
1290  graph_builder_->bytecode_iterator().current_offset());
1291  saved_states_.push(IteratorsStates(
1292  graph_builder_->current_exception_handler(),
1293  graph_builder_->source_position_iterator().GetState()));
1294  }
1295 
1296  // Finishing by advancing to the OSR entry
1297  graph_builder_->AdvanceIteratorsTo(osr_entry);
1298 
1299  // Enters all remaining exception handler which end before the OSR loop
1300  // so that on next call of VisitSingleBytecode they will get popped from
1301  // the exception handlers stack.
1302  graph_builder_->ExitThenEnterExceptionHandlers(osr_entry);
1303  graph_builder_->set_currently_peeled_loop_offset(
1304  graph_builder_->bytecode_analysis()
1305  .GetLoopInfoFor(osr_entry)
1306  .parent_offset());
1307  }
1308 
1309  void RestoreState(int target_offset, int new_parent_offset) {
1310  graph_builder_->bytecode_iterator().SetOffset(target_offset);
1311  // In case of a return, we must not build loop exits for
1312  // not-yet-built outer loops.
1313  graph_builder_->set_currently_peeled_loop_offset(new_parent_offset);
1314  IteratorsStates saved_state = saved_states_.top();
1315  graph_builder_->source_position_iterator().RestoreState(
1316  saved_state.source_iterator_state_);
1317  graph_builder_->set_current_exception_handler(
1318  saved_state.exception_handler_index_);
1319  saved_states_.pop();
1320  }
1321 
1322  private:
1323  struct IteratorsStates {
1324  int exception_handler_index_;
1325  SourcePositionTableIterator::IndexAndPositionState source_iterator_state_;
1326 
1327  IteratorsStates(int exception_handler_index,
1328  SourcePositionTableIterator::IndexAndPositionState
1329  source_iterator_state)
1330  : exception_handler_index_(exception_handler_index),
1331  source_iterator_state_(source_iterator_state) {}
1332  };
1333 
1334  BytecodeGraphBuilder* graph_builder_;
1335  ZoneStack<IteratorsStates> saved_states_;
1336 };

1338 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::RemoveMergeEnvironmentsBeforeOffset(
1339  int limit_offset) {
1340  if (!merge_environments_.empty()) {
1341  ZoneMap<int, Environment*>::iterator it = merge_environments_.begin();
1342  ZoneMap<int, Environment*>::iterator stop_it = merge_environments_.end();
1343  while (it != stop_it && it->first <= limit_offset) {
1344  it = merge_environments_.erase(it);
1345  }
1346  }
1347 }

1371 // We will iterate through the OSR loop, then its parent, and so on
1372 // until we have reached the outmost loop containing the OSR loop. We do
1373 // not generate nodes for anything before the outermost loop.
1374 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::AdvanceToOsrEntryAndPeelLoops() {
1375  environment()->FillWithOsrValues();
1376 
1377  // The entry stack check has to happen *before* initialising the OSR prelude;
1378  // it has to happen before setting up exception handlers, so that the
1379  // optimized code can't accidentally catch a failingstack with a OSR-ed loop
1380  // inside a try-catch, e.g.
1381  //
1382  // try {
1383  // loop { OSR(); }
1384  // } catch {
1385  // // Ignore failed stack check.
1386  // }
1387  BuildOSREntryStackCheck();
1388 
1389  OsrIteratorState iterator_states(this);
1390  iterator_states.ProcessOsrPrelude();
1391  int osr_entry = bytecode_analysis().osr_entry_point();
1392  CHECK_EQ(bytecode_iterator().current_offset(), osr_entry);
1393 
1394  // Suppose we have n nested loops, loop_0 being the outermost one, and
1395  // loop_n being the OSR loop. We start iterating the bytecode at the header
1396  // of loop_n (the OSR loop), and then we peel the part of the the body of
1397  // loop_{n-1} following the end of loop_n. We then rewind the iterator to
1398  // the header of loop_{n-1}, and so on until we have partly peeled loop 0.
1399  // The full loop_0 body will be generating with the rest of the function,
1400  // outside the OSR generation.
1401 
1402  // To do so, if we are visiting a loop, we continue to visit what's left
1403  // of its parent, and then when reaching the parent's JumpLoop, we do not
1404  // create any jump for that but rewind the bytecode iterator to visit the
1405  // parent loop entirely, and so on.
1406 
1407  int current_parent_offset =
1408  bytecode_analysis().GetLoopInfoFor(osr_entry).parent_offset();
1409  while (current_parent_offset != -1) {
1410  const LoopInfo& current_parent_loop =
1411  bytecode_analysis().GetLoopInfoFor(current_parent_offset);
1412  // We iterate until the back edge of the parent loop, which we detect by
1413  // the offset that the JumpLoop targets.
1414  for (; !bytecode_iterator().done(); bytecode_iterator().Advance()) {
1415  if (bytecode_iterator().current_bytecode() ==
1416  interpreter::Bytecode::kJumpLoop &&
1417  bytecode_iterator().GetJumpTargetOffset() == current_parent_offset) {
1418  // Reached the end of the current parent loop.
1419  break;
1420  }
1421  VisitSingleBytecode();
1422  }
1423  DCHECK(!bytecode_iterator()
1424  .done()); // Should have found the loop's jump target.
1425 
1426  // We also need to take care of the merge environments and exceptions
1427  // handlers here because the omitted JumpLoop bytecode can still be the
1428  // target of jumps or the first bytecode after a try block.
1429  ExitThenEnterExceptionHandlers(bytecode_iterator().current_offset());
1430  SwitchToMergeEnvironment(bytecode_iterator().current_offset());
1431 
1432  // This jump is the jump of our parent loop, which is not yet created.
1433  // So we do not build the jump nodes, but restore the bytecode and the
1434  // SourcePosition iterators to the values they had when we were visiting
1435  // the offset pointed at by the JumpLoop we've just reached.
1436  // We have already built nodes for inner loops, but now we will
1437  // iterate again over them and build new nodes corresponding to the same
1438  // bytecode offsets. Any jump or reference to this inner loops must now
1439  // point to the new nodes we will build, hence we clear the relevant part
1440  // of the environment.
1441  // Completely clearing the environment is not possible because merge
1442  // environments for forward jumps out of the loop need to be preserved
1443  // (e.g. a return or a labeled break in the middle of a loop).
1444  RemoveMergeEnvironmentsBeforeOffset(bytecode_iterator().current_offset());
1445  iterator_states.RestoreState(current_parent_offset,
1446  current_parent_loop.parent_offset());
1447  current_parent_offset = current_parent_loop.parent_offset();
1448  }
1449 }

1451 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitSingleBytecode() {
1452  tick_counter_->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
1453  int current_offset = bytecode_iterator().current_offset();
1454  UpdateSourceAndBytecodePosition(current_offset);
1455  ExitThenEnterExceptionHandlers(current_offset);
1456  DCHECK_GE(exception_handlers_.empty() ? current_offset
1457  : exception_handlers_.top().end_offset_,
1458  current_offset);
1459  SwitchToMergeEnvironment(current_offset);
1460 
1461  if (environment() != nullptr) {
1462  BuildLoopHeaderEnvironment(current_offset);
1463 
1464  switch (bytecode_iterator().current_bytecode()) {
1465 #define BYTECODE_CASE(name, ...) \
1466  case interpreter::Bytecode::k##name: \
1467  Visit##name(); \
1468  break;
1469  BYTECODE_LIST(BYTECODE_CASE, BYTECODE_CASE)
1470 #undef BYTECODE_CASE
1471  }
1472  }
1473 }

1475 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitBytecodes() {
1476  if (!bytecode_analysis().resume_jump_targets().empty()) {
1477  environment()->BindGeneratorState(
1478  jsgraph()->SmiConstant(JSGeneratorObject::kGeneratorExecuting));
1479  }
1480 
1481  if (osr_) {
1482  // Make sure we're at a valid OSR entrypoint.
1483  // This is also a defense-in-depth check to make sure that we're not
1484  // compiling invalid bytecode if the OSR offset is wrong (e.g. because it
1485  // belongs to different bytecode).
1486  int osr_offset = bytecode_analysis().osr_bailout_id().ToInt();
1487  int osr_entry = bytecode_analysis().osr_entry_point();
1488  interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator it(bytecode_array().object());
1489  it.AdvanceTo(osr_offset);
1490  CHECK(it.CurrentBytecodeIsValidOSREntry());
1491  CHECK_EQ(osr_entry, it.GetJumpTargetOffset());
1492 
1493  // We peel the OSR loop and any outer loop containing it except that we
1494  // leave the nodes corresponding to the whole outermost loop (including
1495  // the last copies of the loops it contains) to be generated by the normal
1496  // bytecode iteration below.
1497  AdvanceToOsrEntryAndPeelLoops();
1498  } else {
1499  BuildFunctionEntryStackCheck();
1500  }
1501 
1502  for (; !bytecode_iterator().done(); bytecode_iterator().Advance()) {
1503  VisitSingleBytecode();
1504  }
1505 
1506  DCHECK(exception_handlers_.empty());
1507 }

1804 BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment*
1805 BytecodeGraphBuilder::CheckContextExtensionAtDepth(
1806  Environment* slow_environment, uint32_t depth, ContextMode context_mode) {
1807  Node* extension_slot =
1808  NewNode(context_mode == ContextMode::kHasContextCells
1809  ? javascript()->LoadContext(depth, Context::EXTENSION_INDEX)
1810  : javascript()->LoadContextNoCell(
1811  depth, Context::EXTENSION_INDEX, false));
1812  Node* check_no_extension =
1813  NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), extension_slot,
1814  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
1815  NewBranch(check_no_extension);
1816  {
1817  SubEnvironment sub_environment(this);
1818  NewIfFalse();
1819  // If there is an extension, merge into the slow path.
1820  if (slow_environment == nullptr) {
1821  slow_environment = environment();
1822  NewMerge();
1823  } else {
1824  slow_environment->Merge(environment(),
1825  bytecode_analysis().GetInLivenessFor(
1826  bytecode_iterator().current_offset()));
1827  }
1828  }
1829  NewIfTrue();
1830  // Do nothing on if there is no extension, eventually falling through to
1831  // the fast path.
1832  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(slow_environment);
1833  return slow_environment;
1834 }
1835 
1836 OptionalScopeInfoRef BytecodeGraphBuilder::TryGetScopeInfo() {
1837  Node* context = environment()->Context();
1838  switch (context->opcode()) {
1839  case IrOpcode::kJSCreateFunctionContext:
1840  return CreateFunctionContextParametersOf(context->op()).scope_info();
1841  case IrOpcode::kJSCreateBlockContext:
1842  case IrOpcode::kJSCreateCatchContext:
1843  case IrOpcode::kJSCreateWithContext:
1844  return ScopeInfoOf(context->op());
1845  case IrOpcode::kParameter: {
1846  ScopeInfoRef scope_info = shared_info_.scope_info(broker());
1847  if (scope_info.HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
1848  scope_info = scope_info.OuterScopeInfo(broker());
1849  }
1850  return scope_info;
1851  }
1852  default:
1853  return std::nullopt;
1854  }
1855 }

1857 BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment* BytecodeGraphBuilder::CheckContextExtensions(
1858  uint32_t depth) {
1859  OptionalScopeInfoRef maybe_scope_info = TryGetScopeInfo();
1860  if (!maybe_scope_info.has_value()) {
1861  return CheckContextExtensionsSlowPath(depth);
1862  }
1863 
1864  ScopeInfoRef scope_info = maybe_scope_info.value();
1865  // We only need to check up to the last-but-one depth, because an eval
1866  // in the same scope as the variable itself has no way of shadowing it.
1867  Environment* slow_environment = nullptr;
1868  for (uint32_t d = 0; d < depth; d++) {
1869  if (scope_info.HasContextExtensionSlot() &&
1870  !broker()->dependencies()->DependOnEmptyContextExtension(scope_info)) {
1871  // Using EmptyContextExtension dependency is not possible for this
1872  // scope_info, so generate dynamic checks.
1873  // The extension slot is never a context cell.
1874  slow_environment = CheckContextExtensionAtDepth(
1875  slow_environment, d, ContextMode::kNoContextCells);
1876  }
1877  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!scope_info.HasOuterScopeInfo(), d + 1 == depth);
1878  if (scope_info.HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
1879  scope_info = scope_info.OuterScopeInfo(broker());
1880  }
1881  }
1882 
1883  // There should have been at least one slow path generated, otherwise we
1884  // could have already skipped the lookup in the bytecode. The only exception
1885  // is if we replaced all the dynamic checks with code dependencies.
1886  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!v8_flags.empty_context_extension_dep,
1887  slow_environment != nullptr);
1888  return slow_environment;
1889 }
1890 
1891 BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment*
1892 BytecodeGraphBuilder::CheckContextExtensionsSlowPath(uint32_t depth) {
1893  // Output environment where the context has an extension
1894  Environment* slow_environment = nullptr;
1895 
1896  // We only need to check up to the last-but-one depth, because an eval
1897  // in the same scope as the variable itself has no way of shadowing it.
1898  for (uint32_t d = 0; d < depth; d++) {
1899  Node* has_extension = NewNode(javascript()->HasContextExtension(d));
1900 
1901  Environment* undefined_extension_env;
1902  NewBranch(has_extension);
1903  {
1904  SubEnvironment sub_environment(this);
1905  NewIfTrue();
1906  // We don't know if the context has a context extension. If it doesn't,
1907  // the context extension offset might contain a context cell and even
1908  // though this code will not be executed it might still trigger a DCHECK
1909  // at later phases after context specialization which guards against using
1910  // LoadContextNoCell for contexts having ContextCells.
1911  slow_environment = CheckContextExtensionAtDepth(
1912  slow_environment, d, ContextMode::kHasContextCells);
1913  undefined_extension_env = environment();
1914  }
1915  NewIfFalse();
1916  environment()->Merge(undefined_extension_env,
1917  bytecode_analysis().GetInLivenessFor(
1918  bytecode_iterator().current_offset()));
1919  mark_as_needing_eager_checkpoint(true);
1920  // Do nothing on if there is no extension, eventually falling through to
1921  // the fast path.
1922  }
1923 
1924  // There should have been at least one slow path generated, otherwise we could
1925  // have already skipped the lookup in the bytecode.
1926  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(slow_environment);
1927  return slow_environment;
1928 }

1930 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::BuildLdaLookupContextSlot(ContextMode context_mode,
1931  TypeofMode typeof_mode) {
1932  uint32_t depth = bytecode_iterator().GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(2);
1933 
1934  // Check if any context in the depth has an extension.
1935  Environment* slow_environment = CheckContextExtensions(depth);
1936 
1937  // Fast path, do a context load.
1938  {
1939  uint32_t slot_index = bytecode_iterator().GetIndexOperand(1);
1940 
1941  const Operator* op =
1942  context_mode == ContextMode::kHasContextCells
1943  ? javascript()->LoadContext(depth, slot_index)
1944  : javascript()->LoadContextNoCell(depth, slot_index, false);
1945  environment()->BindAccumulator(NewNode(op));
1946  }
1947  if (!slow_environment) {
1948  // The slow path was fully replaced by a set of compilation dependencies.
1949  return;
1950  }
1951 
1952  // Add a merge to the fast environment.
1953  NewMerge();
1954  Environment* fast_environment = environment();
1955 
1956  // Slow path, do a runtime load lookup.
1957  set_environment(slow_environment);
1958  {
1959  Node* name = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(MakeRefForConstantForIndexOperand(0),
1960  broker());
1961 
1962  const Operator* op =
1963  javascript()->CallRuntime(typeof_mode == TypeofMode::kNotInside
1964  ? Runtime::kLoadLookupSlot
1965  : Runtime::kLoadLookupSlotInsideTypeof);
1966  Node* value = NewNode(op, name);
1967  environment()->BindAccumulator(value, Environment::kAttachFrameState);
1968  }
1969 
1970  fast_environment->Merge(environment(),
1971  bytecode_analysis().GetOutLivenessFor(
1972  bytecode_iterator().current_offset()));
1973  set_environment(fast_environment);
1974  mark_as_needing_eager_checkpoint(true);
1975 }

2498 Node* const* BytecodeGraphBuilder::GetCallArgumentsFromRegisters(
2499  Node* callee, Node* receiver, interpreter::Register first_arg,
2500  int arg_count) {
2501  const int arity = JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arg_count);
2502  Node** all = local_zone()->AllocateArray<Node*>(static_cast<size_t>(arity));
2503  int cursor = 0;
2504 
2505  static_assert(JSCallNode::TargetIndex() == 0);
2506  static_assert(JSCallNode::ReceiverIndex() == 1);
2507  static_assert(JSCallNode::FirstArgumentIndex() == 2);
2508  static_assert(JSCallNode::kFeedbackVectorIsLastInput);
2509 
2510  all[cursor++] = callee;
2511  all[cursor++] = receiver;
2512 
2513  // The function arguments are in consecutive registers.
2514  const int arg_base = first_arg.index();
2515  for (int i = 0; i < arg_count; ++i) {
2516  all[cursor++] =
2517  environment()->LookupRegister(interpreter::Register(arg_base + i));
2518  }
2519 
2520  all[cursor++] = feedback_vector_node();
2521 
2522  DCHECK_EQ(cursor, arity);
2523  return all;
2524 }

2526 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::BuildCall(ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode,

2531  receiver_mode);

2538  ComputeCallFeedbackRelation(slot_id);

2541  speculation_mode, call_feedback_relation);
2542  DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsFeedbackCollectingOpcode(op->opcode()));

2548 Node* const* BytecodeGraphBuilder::ProcessCallVarArgs(
2549  ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode, Node* callee,
2550  interpreter::Register first_reg, int arg_count) {
2551  DCHECK_GE(arg_count, 0);
2552  Node* receiver_node;
2553  interpreter::Register first_arg;
2554 
2555  if (receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
2556  // The receiver is implicit (and undefined), the arguments are in
2557  // consecutive registers.
2558  receiver_node = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
2559  first_arg = first_reg;
2560  } else {
2561  // The receiver is the first register, followed by the arguments in the
2562  // consecutive registers.
2563  receiver_node = environment()->LookupRegister(first_reg);
2564  first_arg = interpreter::Register(first_reg.index() + 1);
2565  }
2566 
2567  Node* const* call_args = GetCallArgumentsFromRegisters(callee, receiver_node,
2568  first_arg, arg_count);
2569  return call_args;
2570 }

2572 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::BuildCallVarArgs(ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode) {
2573  DCHECK_EQ(interpreter::Bytecodes::GetReceiverMode(
2574  bytecode_iterator().current_bytecode()),
2575  receiver_mode);
2576  Node* callee =
2577  environment()->LookupRegister(bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(0));
2578  interpreter::Register first_reg = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(1);
2579  size_t reg_count = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterCountOperand(2);
2580  int const slot_id = bytecode_iterator().GetIndexOperand(3);
2581 
2582  int arg_count = receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined
2583  ? static_cast<int>(reg_count)
2584  : static_cast<int>(reg_count) - 1;
2585  Node* const* call_args =
2586  ProcessCallVarArgs(receiver_mode, callee, first_reg, arg_count);
2587  BuildCall(receiver_mode, call_args, JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arg_count),
2588  slot_id);
2589 }

2729 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitCallRuntime() {

2733  size_t reg_count = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterCountOperand(2);
2734

2736  // the node as early as possible.

2746  environment()->BindAccumulator(value, Environment::kAttachFrameState);

2748  // Connect to the end if {function_id} is non-returning.
2749  if (Runtime::IsNonReturning(function_id)) {
2750  // TODO(7099): Investigate if we need LoopExit node here.
2751  Node* control = NewNode(common()->Throw());
2752  MergeControlToLeaveFunction(control);

2800 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitConstruct() {
2801  PrepareEagerCheckpoint();
2802  interpreter::Register callee_reg = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(0);
2803  interpreter::Register first_reg = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(1);
2804  size_t reg_count = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterCountOperand(2);
2805  int const slot_id = bytecode_iterator().GetIndexOperand(3);
2806  FeedbackSource feedback = CreateFeedbackSource(slot_id);
2807 
2808  Node* new_target = environment()->LookupAccumulator();
2809  Node* callee = environment()->LookupRegister(callee_reg);
2810 
2811  CallFrequency frequency = ComputeCallFrequency(slot_id);
2812  const uint32_t arg_count = static_cast<uint32_t>(reg_count);
2813  const uint32_t arity = JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(arg_count);
2814  const Operator* op = javascript()->Construct(arity, frequency, feedback);
2815  DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsFeedbackCollectingOpcode(op->opcode()));
2816  Node* const* args = GetConstructArgumentsFromRegister(callee, new_target,
2817  first_reg, arg_count);
2818  JSTypeHintLowering::LoweringResult lowering = TryBuildSimplifiedConstruct(
2819  op, args, static_cast<int>(arg_count), feedback.slot);
2820  if (lowering.IsExit()) return;
2821 
2822  Node* node = nullptr;
2823  if (lowering.IsSideEffectFree()) {
2824  node = lowering.value();
2825  } else {
2826  DCHECK(!lowering.Changed());
2827  node = MakeNode(op, arity, args);
2828  }
2829  environment()->BindAccumulator(node, Environment::kAttachFrameState);
2830 }

2835  interpreter::Register first_reg = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(1);
2836  size_t reg_count = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterCountOperand(2);
2837  int const slot_id = bytecode_iterator().GetIndexOperand(3);
2838  FeedbackSource feedback = CreateFeedbackSource(slot_id);
2839

2841  Node* callee = environment()->LookupRegister(callee_reg);
2842

2844  const uint32_t arg_count = static_cast<uint32_t>(reg_count);
2845  const uint32_t arity = JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(arg_count);
2846  const Operator* op =
2847  javascript()->ConstructWithSpread(arity, frequency, feedback);
2848  DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsFeedbackCollectingOpcode(op->opcode()));

2865 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitConstructForwardAllArgs() {
2866  PrepareEagerCheckpoint();
2867  interpreter::Register callee_reg = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(0);
2868  int const slot_id = bytecode_iterator().GetIndexOperand(1);
2869  FeedbackSource feedback = CreateFeedbackSource(slot_id);
2870  Node* new_target = environment()->LookupAccumulator();
2871  Node* callee = environment()->LookupRegister(callee_reg);
2872  CallFrequency frequency = ComputeCallFrequency(slot_id);
2873 
2874  // Use 0 as a fake argument count.
2875  //
2876  // This op will be later reduced to either a builtin call (in the case of not
2877  // being inlined) or a normal JSConstruct with the inlined arguments
2878  // forwarded.
2879  constexpr int arg_count = 0;
2880  const int arity = JSConstructForwardAllArgsNode::ArityForArgc(arg_count);
2881  Node** construct_args =
2882  local_zone()->AllocateArray<Node*>(static_cast<size_t>(arity));
2883  static_assert(JSConstructForwardAllArgsNode::TargetIndex() == 0);
2884  static_assert(JSConstructForwardAllArgsNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1);
2885  static_assert(JSConstructNode::kFeedbackVectorIsLastInput);
2886  DCHECK_LT(JSConstructForwardAllArgsNode::NewTargetIndex(), arity);
2887  int cursor = 0;
2888  construct_args[cursor++] = callee;
2889  construct_args[cursor++] = new_target;
2890  construct_args[cursor++] = feedback_vector_node();
2891 
2892  const Operator* op =
2893  javascript()->ConstructForwardAllArgs(frequency, feedback);
2894  JSTypeHintLowering::LoweringResult lowering =
2895  TryBuildSimplifiedConstruct(op, construct_args, arg_count, feedback.slot);
2896  if (lowering.IsExit()) return;
2897 
2898  Node* node;
2899  if (lowering.IsSideEffectFree()) {
2900  node = lowering.value();
2901  } else {
2902  DCHECK(!lowering.Changed());
2903  node = MakeNode(op, arity, construct_args);
2904  }
2905 
2906  environment()->BindAccumulator(node, Environment::kAttachFrameState);
2907 }

3095 CallFrequency BytecodeGraphBuilder::ComputeCallFrequency(int slot_id) const {
3096  if (invocation_frequency_.IsUnknown()) return CallFrequency();
3097  FeedbackSlot slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(slot_id);
3098  FeedbackSource source(feedback_vector(), slot);
3099  ProcessedFeedback const& feedback = broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(source);
3100  float feedback_frequency =
3101  feedback.IsInsufficient() ? 0.0f : feedback.AsCall().frequency();
3102  if (feedback_frequency == 0.0f) { // Prevent multiplying zero and infinity.
3103  return CallFrequency(0.0f);
3104  } else {
3105  return CallFrequency(feedback_frequency * invocation_frequency_.value());
3106  }
3107 }

3114  : feedback.AsCall().speculation_mode();

3117 CallFeedbackRelation BytecodeGraphBuilder::ComputeCallFeedbackRelation(
3118  int slot_id) const {
3119  FeedbackSlot slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(slot_id);
3120  FeedbackSource source(feedback_vector(), slot);
3121  ProcessedFeedback const& feedback = broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(source);
3122  if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) return CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated;
3123  CallFeedbackContent call_feedback_content =
3124  feedback.AsCall().call_feedback_content();

3127  : CallFeedbackRelation::kReceiver;

3428  environment()->LookupRegister(bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(0));

3433  TryBuildSimplifiedBinaryOp(op, left, right, slot);
3434  if (lowering.IsExit()) return;
3435

3437  if (lowering.IsSideEffectFree()) {
3438  node = lowering.value();
3439  } else {
3440  DCHECK(!lowering.Changed());
3441  DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsFeedbackCollectingOpcode(op->opcode()));
3442  node = NewNode(op, left, right, feedback_vector_node());

3888 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitSuspendGenerator() {
3889  Node* generator = environment()->LookupRegister(
3890  bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(0));
3891  interpreter::Register first_reg = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(1);
3892  // We assume we are storing a range starting from index 0.
3893  CHECK_EQ(0, first_reg.index());
3894  int register_count =
3895  static_cast<int>(bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterCountOperand(2));
3896  int parameter_count_without_receiver = bytecode_array().parameter_count() - 1;
3897 
3898  Node* suspend_id = jsgraph()->SmiConstant(
3899  bytecode_iterator().GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(3));
3900 
3901  // The offsets used by the bytecode iterator are relative to a different base
3902  // than what is used in the interpreter, hence the addition.
3903  Node* offset =
3904  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(bytecode_iterator().current_offset() +
3905  (BytecodeArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag));
3906 
3907  const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness = bytecode_analysis().GetInLivenessFor(
3908  bytecode_iterator().current_offset());
3909 
3910  // Maybe overallocate the value list since we don't know how many registers
3911  // are live.
3912  // TODO(leszeks): We could get this count from liveness rather than the
3913  // register list.
3914  int value_input_count = 3 + parameter_count_without_receiver + register_count;
3915 
3916  Node** value_inputs = local_zone()->AllocateArray<Node*>(value_input_count);
3917  value_inputs[0] = generator;
3918  value_inputs[1] = suspend_id;
3919  value_inputs[2] = offset;
3920 
3921  int count_written = 0;
3922  // Store the parameters.
3923  for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count_without_receiver; i++) {
3924  value_inputs[3 + count_written++] =
3925  environment()->LookupRegister(bytecode_iterator().GetParameter(i));
3926  }
3927 
3928  // Store the registers.
3929  for (int i = 0; i < register_count; ++i) {
3930  if (liveness == nullptr || liveness->RegisterIsLive(i)) {
3931  int index_in_parameters_and_registers =
3932  parameter_count_without_receiver + i;
3933  while (count_written < index_in_parameters_and_registers) {
3934  value_inputs[3 + count_written++] = jsgraph()->OptimizedOutConstant();
3935  }
3936  value_inputs[3 + count_written++] =
3937  environment()->LookupRegister(interpreter::Register(i));
3938  DCHECK_EQ(count_written, index_in_parameters_and_registers + 1);
3939  }
3940  }
3941 
3942  // Use the actual written count rather than the register count to create the
3943  // node.
3944  MakeNode(javascript()->GeneratorStore(count_written), 3 + count_written,
3945  value_inputs, false);
3946 
3947  // TODO(leszeks): This over-approximates the liveness at exit, only the
3948  // accumulator should be live by this point.
3949  BuildReturn(bytecode_analysis().GetInLivenessFor(
3950  bytecode_iterator().current_offset()));
3951 }

3953 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::BuildSwitchOnGeneratorState(
3954  const ZoneVector<ResumeJumpTarget>& resume_jump_targets,
3955  bool allow_fallthrough_on_executing) {
3956  Node* generator_state = environment()->LookupGeneratorState();
3957 
3958  int extra_cases = allow_fallthrough_on_executing ? 2 : 1;
3959  NewSwitch(generator_state,
3960  static_cast<int>(resume_jump_targets.size() + extra_cases));
3961  for (const ResumeJumpTarget& target : resume_jump_targets) {
3962  SubEnvironment sub_environment(this);
3963  NewIfValue(target.suspend_id());
3964  if (target.is_leaf()) {
3965  // Mark that we are resuming executing.
3966  environment()->BindGeneratorState(
3967  jsgraph()->SmiConstant(JSGeneratorObject::kGeneratorExecuting));
3968  }
3969  // Jump to the target offset, whether it's a loop header or the resume.
3970  MergeIntoSuccessorEnvironment(target.target_offset());
3971  }
3972 
3973  {
3974  SubEnvironment sub_environment(this);
3975  // We should never hit the default case (assuming generator state cannot be
3976  // corrupted), so abort if we do.
3977  // TODO(leszeks): Maybe only check this in debug mode, and otherwise use
3978  // the default to represent one of the cases above/fallthrough below?
3979  NewIfDefault();
3980  NewNode(simplified()->RuntimeAbort(AbortReason::kInvalidJumpTableIndex));
3981  // TODO(7099): Investigate if we need LoopExit here.
3982  Node* control = NewNode(common()->Throw());
3983  MergeControlToLeaveFunction(control);
3984  }
3985 
3986  if (allow_fallthrough_on_executing) {
3987  // If we are executing (rather than resuming), and we allow it, just fall
3988  // through to the actual loop body.
3989  NewIfValue(JSGeneratorObject::kGeneratorExecuting);
3990  } else {
3991  // Otherwise, this environment is dead.
3992  set_environment(nullptr);
3993  }
3994 }

3996 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitSwitchOnGeneratorState() {
3997  Node* generator =
3998  environment()->LookupRegister(bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(0));
3999 
4000  Node* generator_is_undefined =
4001  NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), generator,
4002  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
4003 
4004  NewBranch(generator_is_undefined);
4005  {
4006  SubEnvironment resume_env(this);
4007  NewIfFalse();
4008 
4009  Node* generator_state =
4010  NewNode(javascript()->GeneratorRestoreContinuation(), generator);
4011  environment()->BindGeneratorState(generator_state);
4012 
4013  Node* generator_context =
4014  NewNode(javascript()->GeneratorRestoreContextNoCell(), generator);
4015  environment()->SetContext(generator_context);
4016 
4017  BuildSwitchOnGeneratorState(bytecode_analysis().resume_jump_targets(),
4018  false);
4019  }
4020 
4021  // Fallthrough for the first-call case.
4022  NewIfTrue();
4023 }

4025 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitResumeGenerator() {
4026  Node* generator =
4027  environment()->LookupRegister(bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(0));
4028  interpreter::Register first_reg = bytecode_iterator().GetRegisterOperand(1);
4029  // We assume we are restoring registers starting from index 0.
4030  CHECK_EQ(0, first_reg.index());
4031 
4032  const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness = bytecode_analysis().GetOutLivenessFor(
4033  bytecode_iterator().current_offset());
4034 
4035  int parameter_count_without_receiver = bytecode_array().parameter_count() - 1;
4036 
4037  // Mapping between registers and array indices must match that used in
4038  // InterpreterAssembler::ExportParametersAndRegisterFile.
4039  for (int i = 0; i < environment()->register_count(); ++i) {
4040  if (liveness == nullptr || liveness->RegisterIsLive(i)) {
4041  Node* value = NewNode(javascript()->GeneratorRestoreRegister(
4042  parameter_count_without_receiver + i),
4043  generator);
4044  environment()->BindRegister(interpreter::Register(i), value);
4045  }
4046  }
4047 
4048  // Update the accumulator with the generator's input_or_debug_pos.
4049  Node* input_or_debug_pos =
4050  NewNode(javascript()->GeneratorRestoreInputOrDebugPos(), generator);
4051  environment()->BindAccumulator(input_or_debug_pos);
4052 }

4069 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::SwitchToMergeEnvironment(int current_offset) {
4070  auto it = merge_environments_.find(current_offset);
4071  if (it != merge_environments_.end()) {
4072  mark_as_needing_eager_checkpoint(true);
4073  if (environment() != nullptr) {
4074  it->second->Merge(environment(),
4075  bytecode_analysis().GetInLivenessFor(current_offset));
4076  }

4078  }

4081 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::BuildLoopHeaderEnvironment(int current_offset) {
4082  if (bytecode_analysis().IsLoopHeader(current_offset)) {
4083  mark_as_needing_eager_checkpoint(true);
4084  const LoopInfo& loop_info =
4085  bytecode_analysis().GetLoopInfoFor(current_offset);
4086  const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness =
4087  bytecode_analysis().GetInLivenessFor(current_offset);
4088 
4089  const auto& resume_jump_targets = loop_info.resume_jump_targets();
4090  bool generate_suspend_switch = !resume_jump_targets.empty();
4091 
4092  // Add loop header.
4093  environment()->PrepareForLoop(loop_info.assignments(), liveness);
4094 
4095  // Store a copy of the environment so we can connect merged back edge inputs
4096  // to the loop header.
4097  merge_environments_[current_offset] = environment()->Copy();
4098 
4099  // If this loop contains resumes, create a new switch just after the loop
4100  // for those resumes.
4101  if (generate_suspend_switch) {
4102  BuildSwitchOnGeneratorState(loop_info.resume_jump_targets(), true);
4103 
4104  // TODO(leszeks): At this point we know we are executing rather than
4105  // resuming, so we should be able to prune off the phis in the environment
4106  // related to the resume path.
4107 
4108  // Set the generator state to a known constant.
4109  environment()->BindGeneratorState(
4110  jsgraph()->SmiConstant(JSGeneratorObject::kGeneratorExecuting));
4111  }
4112  }
4113 }

4115 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::MergeIntoSuccessorEnvironment(int target_offset) {
4116  BuildLoopExitsForBranch(target_offset);
4117  Environment*& merge_environment = merge_environments_[target_offset];
4118 
4119  if (merge_environment == nullptr) {
4120  // Append merge nodes to the environment. We may merge here with another
4121  // environment. So add a place holder for merge nodes. We may add redundant
4122  // but will be eliminated in a later pass.
4123  NewMerge();
4124  merge_environment = environment();
4125  } else {
4126  // Merge any values which are live coming into the successor.
4127  merge_environment->Merge(
4128  environment(), bytecode_analysis().GetInLivenessFor(target_offset));
4129  }
4130  set_environment(nullptr);
4131 }

4138 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::BuildLoopExitsForBranch(int target_offset) {

4140  // Only build loop exits for forward edges.
4141  if (target_offset > origin_offset) {
4142  BuildLoopExitsUntilLoop(
4143  bytecode_analysis().GetLoopOffsetFor(target_offset),
4144  bytecode_analysis().GetInLivenessFor(target_offset));
4145  }

4148 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::BuildLoopExitsUntilLoop(
4149  int loop_offset, const BytecodeLivenessState* liveness) {
4150  int origin_offset = bytecode_iterator().current_offset();
4151  int current_loop = bytecode_analysis().GetLoopOffsetFor(origin_offset);
4152  // The limit_offset is the stop offset for building loop exists, used for OSR.
4153  // It prevents the creations of loopexits for loops which do not exist.
4154  loop_offset = std::max(loop_offset, currently_peeled_loop_offset_);
4155 
4156  while (loop_offset < current_loop) {
4157  Node* loop_node = merge_environments_[current_loop]->GetControlDependency();
4158  const LoopInfo& loop_info =
4159  bytecode_analysis().GetLoopInfoFor(current_loop);
4160  environment()->PrepareForLoopExit(loop_node, loop_info.assignments(),
4161  liveness);
4162  current_loop = loop_info.parent_offset();
4163  }
4164 }

4415 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::ApplyEarlyReduction(
4416  JSTypeHintLowering::LoweringResult reduction) {
4417  if (reduction.IsExit()) {
4418  MergeControlToLeaveFunction(reduction.control());
4419  } else if (reduction.IsSideEffectFree()) {
4420  environment()->UpdateEffectDependency(reduction.effect());
4421  environment()->UpdateControlDependency(reduction.control());
4422  } else {
4423  DCHECK(!reduction.Changed());
4424  // At the moment, we assume side-effect free reduction. To support
4425  // side-effects, we would have to invalidate the eager checkpoint,
4426  // so that deoptimization does not repeat the side effect.
4427  }
4428 }

4431  if (size > input_buffer_size_) {
4432  size = size + kInputBufferSizeIncrement + input_buffer_size_;
4433  input_buffer_ = local_zone()->AllocateArray<Node*>(size);
4434  input_buffer_size_ = size;
4435  }
4436  return input_buffer_;
4437 }

4439 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::ExitThenEnterExceptionHandlers(int current_offset) {
4440  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4441  HandlerTable table(bytecode_array().handler_table_address(),
4442  bytecode_array().handler_table_size(),
4443  HandlerTable::kRangeBasedEncoding);
4444 
4445  // Potentially exit exception handlers.
4446  while (!exception_handlers_.empty()) {
4447  int current_end = exception_handlers_.top().end_offset_;
4448  if (current_offset < current_end) break; // Still covered by range.
4449  exception_handlers_.pop();
4450  }
4451 
4452  // Potentially enter exception handlers.
4453  int num_entries = table.NumberOfRangeEntries();
4454  while (current_exception_handler_ < num_entries) {
4455  int next_start = table.GetRangeStart(current_exception_handler_);
4456  if (current_offset < next_start) break; // Not yet covered by range.
4457  int next_end = table.GetRangeEnd(current_exception_handler_);
4458  int next_handler = table.GetRangeHandler(current_exception_handler_);
4459  int context_register = table.GetRangeData(current_exception_handler_);
4460  exception_handlers_.push(
4461  {next_start, next_end, next_handler, context_register});
4462  current_exception_handler_++;
4463  }
4464 }

4466 Node* BytecodeGraphBuilder::MakeNode(const Operator* op, int value_input_count,
4467  Node* const* value_inputs,
4468  bool incomplete) {
4469  DCHECK_EQ(op->ValueInputCount(), value_input_count);
4470  // Parameter nodes must be created through GetParameter.
4471  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
4472  op->opcode() == IrOpcode::kParameter,
4473  (nullptr == cached_parameters_[static_cast<std::size_t>(
4474  ParameterIndexOf(op) - ParameterInfo::kMinIndex)]));
4475 
4476  bool has_context = OperatorProperties::HasContextInput(op);
4477  bool has_frame_state = OperatorProperties::HasFrameStateInput(op);
4478  bool has_control = op->ControlInputCount() == 1;
4479  bool has_effect = op->EffectInputCount() == 1;
4480 
4481  DCHECK_LT(op->ControlInputCount(), 2);
4482  DCHECK_LT(op->EffectInputCount(), 2);
4483 
4484  Node* result = nullptr;
4485  if (!has_context && !has_frame_state && !has_control && !has_effect) {
4486  result = graph()->NewNode(op, value_input_count, value_inputs, incomplete);
4487  } else {
4488  bool inside_handler = !exception_handlers_.empty();
4489  int input_count_with_deps = value_input_count;
4490  if (has_context) ++input_count_with_deps;
4491  if (has_frame_state) ++input_count_with_deps;
4492  if (has_control) ++input_count_with_deps;
4493  if (has_effect) ++input_count_with_deps;
4494  Node** buffer = EnsureInputBufferSize(input_count_with_deps);
4495  if (value_input_count > 0) {
4496  memcpy(buffer, value_inputs, kSystemPointerSize * value_input_count);
4497  }
4498  Node** current_input = buffer + value_input_count;
4499  if (has_context) {
4500  *current_input++ = OperatorProperties::NeedsExactContext(op)
4501  ? environment()->Context()
4502  : native_context_node();
4503  }
4504  if (has_frame_state) {
4505  // The frame state will be inserted later. Here we misuse the {Dead} node
4506  // as a sentinel to be later overwritten with the real frame state by the
4507  // calls to {PrepareFrameState} within individual visitor methods.
4508  *current_input++ = jsgraph()->Dead();
4509  }
4510  if (has_effect) {
4511  *current_input++ = environment()->GetEffectDependency();
4512  }
4513  if (has_control) {
4514  *current_input++ = environment()->GetControlDependency();
4515  }
4516  result = graph()->NewNode(op, input_count_with_deps, buffer, incomplete);
4517  // Update the current control dependency for control-producing nodes.
4518  if (result->op()->ControlOutputCount() > 0) {
4519  environment()->UpdateControlDependency(result);
4520  }
4521  // Update the current effect dependency for effect-producing nodes.
4522  if (result->op()->EffectOutputCount() > 0) {
4523  environment()->UpdateEffectDependency(result);
4524  }
4525  // Add implicit exception continuation for throwing nodes.
4526  if (!result->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoThrow) && inside_handler) {
4527  int handler_offset = exception_handlers_.top().handler_offset_;
4528  int context_index = exception_handlers_.top().context_register_;
4529  interpreter::Register context_register(context_index);
4530  Environment* success_env = environment()->Copy();
4531  const Operator* if_exception = common()->IfException();
4532  Node* effect = environment()->GetEffectDependency();
4533  Node* on_exception = graph()->NewNode(if_exception, effect, result);
4534  Node* context = environment()->LookupRegister(context_register);
4535  environment()->UpdateControlDependency(on_exception);
4536  environment()->UpdateEffectDependency(on_exception);
4537  environment()->BindAccumulator(on_exception);
4538  environment()->SetContext(context);
4539  MergeIntoSuccessorEnvironment(handler_offset);
4540  set_environment(success_env);
4541  }
4542  // Add implicit success continuation for throwing nodes.
4543  if (!result->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoThrow) && inside_handler) {
4544  const Operator* if_success = common()->IfSuccess();
4545  Node* on_success = graph()->NewNode(if_success, result);
4546  environment()->UpdateControlDependency(on_success);
4547  }
4548  // Ensure checkpoints are created after operations with side-effects.
4549  if (has_effect && !result->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoWrite)) {
4550  mark_as_needing_eager_checkpoint(true);
4551  }
4552  }
4553 
4554  return result;
4555 }

4576 Node* BytecodeGraphBuilder::MergeControl(Node* control, Node* other) {
4577  int inputs = control->op()->ControlInputCount() + 1;
4578  if (control->opcode() == IrOpcode::kLoop) {
4579  // Control node for loop exists, add input.
4580  const Operator* op = common()->Loop(inputs);
4581  control->AppendInput(graph_zone(), other);
4582  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(control, op);
4583  } else if (control->opcode() == IrOpcode::kMerge) {
4584  // Control node for merge exists, add input.
4585  const Operator* op = common()->Merge(inputs);
4586  control->AppendInput(graph_zone(), other);
4587  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(control, op);
4588  } else {
4589  // Control node is a singleton, introduce a merge.
4590  const Operator* op = common()->Merge(inputs);
4591  Node* merge_inputs[] = {control, other};
4592  control = graph()->NewNode(op, arraysize(merge_inputs), merge_inputs, true);
4593  }
4594  return control;
4595 }

4597 Node* BytecodeGraphBuilder::MergeEffect(Node* value, Node* other,
4598  Node* control) {
4599  int inputs = control->op()->ControlInputCount();
4600  if (value->opcode() == IrOpcode::kEffectPhi &&
4601  NodeProperties::GetControlInput(value) == control) {
4602  // Phi already exists, add input.
4603  value->InsertInput(graph_zone(), inputs - 1, other);
4604  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(value, common()->EffectPhi(inputs));
4605  } else if (value != other) {
4606  // Phi does not exist yet, introduce one.
4607  value = NewEffectPhi(inputs, value, control);
4608  value->ReplaceInput(inputs - 1, other);
4609  }
4610  return value;
4611 }

4613 Node* BytecodeGraphBuilder::MergeValue(Node* value, Node* other,
4614  Node* control) {
4615  int inputs = control->op()->ControlInputCount();
4616  if (value->opcode() == IrOpcode::kPhi &&
4617  NodeProperties::GetControlInput(value) == control) {
4618  // Phi already exists, add input.
4619  value->InsertInput(graph_zone(), inputs - 1, other);
4620  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4621  value, common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, inputs));
4622  } else if (value != other) {
4623  // Phi does not exist yet, introduce one.
4624  value = NewPhi(inputs, value, control);
4625  value->ReplaceInput(inputs - 1, other);
4626  }
4627  return value;
4628 }

4630 void BytecodeGraphBuilder::UpdateSourceAndBytecodePosition(int offset) {
4631  if (node_origins_) {
4632  node_origins_->SetCurrentBytecodePosition(offset);
4633  }
4634  if (source_position_iterator().done()) return;
4635  if (source_position_iterator().code_offset() == offset) {
4636  source_positions_->SetCurrentPosition(SourcePosition(
4637  source_position_iterator().source_position().ScriptOffset(),
4638  start_position_.InliningId()));
4639  source_position_iterator().Advance();
4640  } else {
4641  DCHECK_GT(source_position_iterator().code_offset(), offset);
4642  }
4643 }
